y artists use in relation to the exhibition catalogue? How do they present their works and themselves, and what does the catalogue teach us about the notion of art? How does one translate and rework an exhibition into a book? This volume analyzes example texts and images from exhibition catalogues with regard to the history and conventions of this medium.   aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn German.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 23. Jun 2020) 0aArtvCatalogs. 0aArtvDocumentation. 0aArtxCatalogs. 0aArtxDocumentation. 0aAusstellung. 0aAusstellungskatalog. 0aKünstlerbuch. 7aART / Collections, Catalogs, Exhibitions / General.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Plus eBook-Package 2015z978311070098508iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Arts and Architecture 2014z9783110369595oZDB-23-DKA08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Complete Package 2014z9783110369526oZDB-23-DGG0 cEPUBz97831103823270 cprintz978311033210040uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978311033219340uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9783110332193423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9783110332193.jpg  a978-3-11-070098-5  DG Plus eBook-Package 2015b2015  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_MUAR  aEBA_DGALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aEBA_STMALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA12STME  aPDA5EBK  aZDB-23-DGGb2014  aZDB-23-DKAb2014